# Theme System

All themes are defined in `src/lib/themes.ts`. There are 11 themes (6 dark, 5 light).

## Rules

- NEVER hardcode hex colors in CSS. Use `var(--token)` from the design system.
- When adding a new CSS variable, define it in `:root` (global.css) AND in every theme in `themes.ts`.
- `--bg-header` is for table column headers — distinct from `--bg-primary`/`--bg-secondary`.
- Semi-transparent `rgba()` overlays for status backgrounds (success/error result banners) are acceptable since they adapt to any theme.
- Button text on colored backgrounds (accent, error) must use `var(--text-inverse)`, not `#fff`.
- Input hover borders must use `var(--border)`, not `rgba(255,255,255,...)` which breaks on light themes.
- Scrollbar colors: thumb uses `var(--border-subtle)`, thumb:hover uses `var(--bg-active)`.
